message.content: Before Cam broke his arm, he typed 9 words per minute, so in 5 minutes he would type 9 * 5 = 45 words. After breaking his arm, he could only type 6 words per minute, and so in 5 minutes he would type 6 * 5 = 30 words. To find the difference between the number of words typed before and after the break, subtract the smaller number from the larger: 45 - 30 = 15. So, Cam could type 15 more words in 5 minutes before he broke his arm than after he broke it.
